  "original_title": "\u0d8b\u0db4\u0dd9\u0dc5 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dae\u0dd2\u0db5\u0dbd \u0db1\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2 - 171497  \u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dc0\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Result Released - 171497 Varam",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The results of the General Certificate of Education A Level 2021 examination have been released. The exam results can be obtained through the website www.doenets.lk and www.results.exams.gov.lk of the examination department.",
        "A total of 272682 applicants appeared in this year's A-level examination, 236035 school applicants and 36647 private applicants.",
        "According to the examination department, 171497 students have qualified for university admission based on the results of the examination.",
        "The department also says that this group is 62.9 percent of the total number of students who applied for the A-level examination.",
        "The results of 49 applicants including 37 school applicants and 12 private applicants have been withheld."
      ],
